The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for maintaining connectivity among a swarm of robots, which is a common problem in multi-agent systems (MAS) and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also deals with robot failures and unstable links, which are typical issues in robotics, suggesting that cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely category. The algorithm aims to guarantee bandwidth and reliability, which are related to control and system theory, respectively, indicating that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category. The paper also involves networked systems, which can be associated with cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a decentralized algorithm, which can be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
